caption: Kind staff, great food, great pricing. Easily walkable from DTSS.
My favorite sushi place in the area, by far!
This spot is excellent! Affordable rates, big dishes and the staff members are regularly very friendly.
Would certainly recommend trying out this place. Great atmosphere, tasty food, awesome customer service. They never disappoint.
Everything is delicious, the people are so nice, and I know for certain we'll be back soon.

Ikko was always my favorite sushi place back in the early 2010s. I just tried them again for the first time in many years, and wow--their quality is really a cut above. Every ingredient is high quality and thoughtfully prepared. A true gem of a restaurant!

Sushi is typically a more expensive meal for us, but this will be our go to place when we decide to treat ourselves.

This place is a great neighborhood standby. I’m pretty picky about sushi and I trust this place for both sashimi and for more fun, Americanized special rolls. I’ve had their non-sushi dishes too, and I really enjoy most of the menu. Their selection isn’t huge but I think that helps them maintain super fresh ingredients. They are have a great system set up for minimal contact when picking up orders, and everything is carefully packaged. It can take a while for them to pull and order together (especially if it’s a big order), but they have always given me accurate estimates of when things will be ready when I place my order.
The place offers a nice range of delicious food. I liked eating here. Staff members are always helpful, pricing is fair and the place is always well organised.

I celebrated my graduation this evening in this great place. I am glad to say that we passed a pleasant evening and the restaurant was indeed one of the reasons for the outstanding event. The crew  contributed in a lovely style, the food was yummy and my guests were very  delighted. We shall definitely come back again for more joyful events. Thank you very much.

Great local spot, it may seem tiny at first, but the manager has a big personality and a wide selection of sushi cuts you won't find in your general sushi bar in Silver Spring.  The ambiance is warmly lit and family friendly. The atmosphere is cheerful and bright.  Again, the selection of sakes and sushi is very different from the norm. They have hot and cold sakes, the traditional appetizers, a range of nigiri cuts and fun creative sushi rolls. What I like best is the flavor variety-- sometimes sushi can taste like one large plate of the same cold raw fish. But thankfully, Ikko knows how to showcase a larger flavor profile without the overuse of sauces and tempuras to make their mark.  Though I am moving out of the Silver Spring area soon, I'll be back to Ikko for sure. It's a top taste if you are ever in the neighborhood!

The sushi here is really good with a cute local flair (many rolls being named for nearby landmarks/locations). It's a workday eating spot for folks at the NOAA building on East-West, which means that during weekends and off hours there's usually plenty of seats to go around. If you do go on a weekday and the weather's nice, you might try sitting in their outdoor seating area near the NOAA wave pool.  Service here is solid, attentive but not overly bothering. The one drawback is the wait time for non-sushi dishes. These meals include things like beef bowls, chicken teriyaki, etc and are all quite good... but you'll be waiting for them for ten or so minutes after all the sushi has already arrived.  Public parking garage nearby below the NOAA building, free parking on weekends or evenings after 7.

Located at the bottom of the Bennington Apartments complex.  I had the Ikko Dragon roll and Spider roll ($29.66 after taxes). One good thing was they didn't drown the rolls in sauce. However, the eel itself was a little bland and tasteless. The soft shell crab was fried okay (didn't really have the fresh fried taste). The meat wasn't as sweet as I had hoped. The portion size was fine. I was definitely full after the meal. One nice touch is that they give you a piece of watermelon and orange at the end of your meal. A lot of restaurants don't do this anymore and it was a welcomed touch.  Service was excellent and they were very attentive. There are quite a few workers there for dinner service so I would expect it as so. The decor was nice and they have outside seating. They also have a minimum $10 charge for cc use.  Overall the food was decent and I'd like to come back to try their sashimi. I would recommend this place.

Consistently great service and good, affordable food. My favorites are: the Bu Bim Bap beef rice bowl and the teriyaki beef and kalbi dinner, as well as the spicy tuna and various California rolls. Friends have enjoyed the eel and the monument rolls.  One experience that stands out to me: I was unwell and just needed good food I didn't have to stand up and cook, so I ordered from them. When I went to pick it up the owner saw that I was sick and not only wished me well, but gave me a HUGE container of miso soup for free to help me get well. I was so touched because I felt so poorly and her kindness really touched me.  I have recommended this spot to visiting family and they too had a great experience with the food AND service.  Tip: IKKO Sushi is a neighborhood staple (popular and folks like to linger a bit over their meal) and it offers Groupons fairly often, so it is bustling on the weekends. Therefore, you're well-advised to make a reservation.

I tried asking her again in different words what type of seating was the bar seating if it's not first come first serve. She responded more aggressively that others were here before me. This is unacceptable behavior and unacceptable responses to their potential customers.
